## Commands

- Install/sync: `uv sync`
- Test: `uv run pytest`
- Lint + format: `uv run ruff check --fix . && uv run ruff format .`
- Type check: `uv run mypy src/`
- Full gate (run before calling any task done): `make check`  <!-- or the equivalent -->

## Environment

- Use `uv` for everything — never `pip install`, `poetry`, or bare `python`.
  Add dependencies with `uv add <pkg>` (dev: `uv add --dev <pkg>`).
- Never edit `uv.lock` by hand; it changes only via uv commands.

## Definition of done

- Lint, type check, and tests all pass locally before you present work as
  complete. Run them; do not assume.
- Never weaken a gate to pass it: no lowering coverage thresholds, no
  skipping/deleting failing tests, no `|| true`, no `--no-verify`.
- If you changed a public API, update its docs in the same change.

## Review boundaries

- Flag — do not silently change — anything touching authentication, payments,
  dependency declarations, lockfiles, `.github/workflows/`, or `.claude/`.
- New dependencies require explicit human sign-off; verify the package exists
  and is established before adding it (agents have hallucinated package names
  that attackers then registered).

